Subject: [PATCH 084/120] dt-bindings: sun6i-dsi: Add VCC-DSI supply property

Most of the Allwinner MIPI DSI controllers are supply with
VCC-DSI pin. which need to supply for some of the boards to
trigger the power.

So, document the supply property so-that the required board
can eable it via device tree.

Signed-off-by: Jagan Teki <jagan@amarulasolutions.com>
Reviewed-by: Rob Herring <robh@kernel.org>
---
 .../bindings/display/allwinner,sun6i-a31-mipi-dsi.yaml       | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/allwinner,sun6i-a31-mipi-dsi.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/allwinner,sun6i-a31-mipi-dsi.yaml
index 47950fced28d..1fe9eecdf35f 100644
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/allwinner,sun6i-a31-mipi-dsi.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/allwinner,sun6i-a31-mipi-dsi.yaml
@@ -50,6 +50,11 @@ properties:
       port should be the input endpoint, usually coming from the
       associated TCON.
 
+  dsi-supply:
+    description:
+      VCC-DSI supply for the DSI encoder
+
+
 patternProperties:
   "^panel@[0-9]+$": true
 
